<paragraph id="8BB4124EFFDBFFF439F9E875FD884164" blockId="8.[151,1436,1349,1734]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis id="B97FCE5CFFDBFFF439F9E875FEF142F4" bold="true" box="[199,358,1385,1410]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Introduction.</emphasis>
The genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B69CDFFDBFFF438D5E876FDD742F7" box="[491,576,1386,1409]" class="Insecta" family="Kermesidae" genus="Kermes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97FCE5CFFDBFFF438D5E876FDD742F7" box="[491,576,1386,1409]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Kermes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the 
<typeStatus id="54B0ACECFFDBFFF43BB0E876FD2942F4" box="[654,702,1386,1410]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">type</typeStatus>
genus of the family 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B69CDFFDBFFF43A95E875FBA342F4" box="[939,1076,1385,1410]" class="Insecta" family="Kermesidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Kermesidae</taxonomicName>
. Some of the synonyms for this genus include 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B69CDFFDBFFF43809E892FDA442D0" authority="Silvestri" authorityName="Silvestri" authorityYear="1911" box="[311,563,1421,1446]" class="Insecta" family="Kermesidae" genus="Kermococcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97FCE5CFFDBFFF43809E892FE5842D3" box="[311,463,1422,1445]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Kermococcus</emphasis>
Silvestri
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B69CDFFDBFFF43B57E891FD3542D0" authority="von Heyden, 1860" authorityName="von Heyden" authorityYear="1860" box="[617,674,1421,1446]" class="Insecta" family="Kermesidae" genus="Talla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97FCE5CFFDBFFF43B57E891FD3542D0" box="[617,674,1421,1446]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Talla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
von Heyden (
<bibRefCitation id="EF9A6FBFFFDBFFF43A00E891FB0242D0" author="Bullington" box="[830,1173,1421,1446]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" refString="Bullington, S. W. &amp; Kosztarab, M. (1985) A revision of the family Kermesidae (Homoptera) in the Nearctic Region based on adult and third instar females) Bulletin of the Virginia Polytechnic Institute and University Research Division, 85, 1 - 118." type="journal article" year="1985">
Bullington &amp; Kosztarab, 
<number id="3DC30069FFDBFFF43D67E891FB0242D0" box="[1113,1173,1421,1446]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1985.0">1985</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). This is the only genus that is found in all regions of the world where 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B69CDFFDBFFF43BF7E8ADFCD842BC" box="[713,847,1457,1482]" class="Insecta" family="Kermesidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Kermesidae</taxonomicName>
species are recorded: the Nearctic region with 
<number id="3DC30069FFDBFFF43CBEE8ADFA0B42BC" box="[1408,1436,1457,1482]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="16.0">16</number>
species, the Oriental and Palaearctic regions both with 
<number id="3DC30069FFDBFFF43BC7E8CAFC824298" box="[761,789,1494,1518]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="23.0">23</number>
species, the latter including the six described in this study from 
<collectingCountry id="F31C52DEFFDBFFF439EAE8E5FE854164" box="[212,274,1529,1554]" name="Israel" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Israel</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF9A6FBFFFDBFFF4381FE8E6FD844164" author="Ben-Dov" box="[289,531,1529,1554]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" refString="Ben-Dov, Y., Miller, D. R. &amp; Gibson, G. A. P. (2013) ScaleNet: a Database of the Scale Insects of the World. Scales in a Region. Query Results. Available from: http: // www. sel. barc. usda. gov / SCALENET / SCALENET. HTM (accessed 1 Mar. 2013)" type="journal article" year="2013">
Ben-Dov 
<emphasis id="B97FCE5CFFDBFFF438AEE8E6FE554164" box="[400,450,1529,1554]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">et al</emphasis>
., 
<number id="3DC30069FFDBFFF438E8E8E6FD844164" box="[470,531,1530,1554]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="2013.0">2013</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB4124EFFDBFFF439F9EB01FDE541B0" blockId="8.[151,1436,1349,1734]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
All 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B69CDFFDBFFF439CCEB02FED04143" box="[242,327,1566,1589]" class="Insecta" family="Kermesidae" genus="Kermes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97FCE5CFFDBFFF439CCEB02FED04143" box="[242,327,1566,1589]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Kermes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species share the following traits in the adult female: presence of (i) a submarginal band of tubular ducts on venter; (ii) multilocular pores ventrally on the abdominal segments, and (iii) a three-segmented labium with 
<number id="3DC30069FFDBFFF439ECEB7AFF794108" box="[210,238,1638,1662]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="14.0">14</number>
setose setae. Our study suggests that the many species currently included in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B69CDFFDBFFF43D56EB7AFB29410B" box="[1128,1214,1638,1661]" class="Insecta" family="Kermesidae" genus="Kermes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97FCE5CFFDBFFF43D56EB7AFB29410B" box="[1128,1214,1638,1661]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Kermes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have a very varied morphology making a generic diagnosis difficult, indicating that further work needs to be done, particularly those described from post-reproductive females.
</paragraph>
